          <Textbox Name="Textbox2">
            <rd:DefaultName>Textbox2</rd:DefaultName>
            <CanGrow>true</CanGrow>
            <KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether>
            <Paragraphs>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>Note:</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontWeight>Bold</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>
The table always shows data starting from January of the year you select in the "From Date" filter, up to the exact day, month, and year you select in the "To Date" filter.
For example, if you set From Date = 03/01/2024 and To Date = 06/15/2024, the table will still show data from January 2024 to June 15, 2024—not from March.
Only the year from the "From Date" is considered, not the month or day.</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Italic</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
            </Paragraphs>
            <Top>0.25917in</Top>
            <Left>0in</Left>
            <Height>0.69792in</Height>
